               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.24.30b &lt;i&gt;saṃvatsaraṃ yajati puṇyaprekṣī&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; This is a difficult line, because the Sanskrit text is lacking. &lt;i&gt;lki&lt;/i&gt;, which can be read if the piece flipped over to the verso is considered, must be from &lt;i&gt;telki&lt;/i&gt; and combined with &lt;i&gt;yam-&lt;/i&gt; it must mean ‘honour’ or ‘sacrifice’ (the equation &lt;i&gt;telki&lt;/i&gt; ~ &lt;i&gt;yajña&lt;/i&gt; is attested in [[THT 541]] a4). [[Bernhard 1965]]’s reconstruction &lt;i&gt;puṇyaprekṣī&lt;/i&gt; is confirmed by &lt;i&gt;yarpo lk· ///&lt;/i&gt;, which must contain a form of &lt;i&gt;ləka-&lt;/i&gt; ‘see’, but his &lt;i&gt;yajati&lt;/i&gt; may have to be turned into &lt;i&gt;yajeta&lt;/i&gt; in view of the opt. in Tocharian B &lt;i&gt;yāmi&lt;/i&gt; (and cf. Dhp.108b &lt;i&gt;yajetha&lt;/i&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.24.30d &lt;i&gt;abhivādanaṃ tv ṛjjugateṣu śreyaḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; After &lt;i&gt;(ke)k(a)moṣ&lt;/i&gt;, the word &lt;i&gt;saim&lt;/i&gt; can be read, but the lower part of the ligature &lt;i&gt;mXā&lt;/i&gt; is unclear. I would expect a form of &lt;i&gt;yam-&lt;/i&gt; ‘to do’ and the following akṣara could either be &lt;i&gt;mi&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;mo&lt;/i&gt;, both giving good possibilities (i.e. either &lt;i&gt;yāmo°&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;yāmi&lt;/i&gt;), but it looks more like &lt;i&gt;m[n]ā&lt;/i&gt;, so that I would like to leave this question open.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.1b &lt;i&gt;piśunair vibhūtinandibhiḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; I expect &lt;i&gt;wṣetstse&lt;/i&gt; or the like as a translation of &lt;i&gt;piśuna&lt;/i&gt;, but there are no rests below the &lt;i&gt;t&lt;/i&gt;. Maybe it is just very badly abraded.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.2a &lt;i&gt;śrāddhebhiḥ peśalebhiś ca&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.2c &lt;i&gt;sākhyaṃ kurvīta saprajñaḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b1.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.4c &lt;i&gt;teṣāṃ hi śrutvā tu subhāṣitāni&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.5a &lt;i&gt;hīyati puruṣo nihīnasevī&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.5c &lt;i&gt;śreṣṭham upagato hy upaiti śraiṣṭhyaṃ&lt;/i&gt;. We clearly read &lt;i&gt;śre&lt;/i&gt;, so probably &lt;i&gt;śre(ṣṭham)&lt;/i&gt;, against Bernhard’s reconstruction &lt;i&gt;śraiṣṭhyaṃ&lt;/i&gt; Uv. 25.5c, just like &lt;i&gt;(śr)e(ṣṭham)&lt;/i&gt; in [[THT 308]] a8.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.6a &lt;i&gt;śreyo hi labhate nityaṃ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.25.6d &lt;i&gt;śīlenopaśamena ca&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</item>
